      "message": "[minor] Line 1969: 🟡 Suggestion: File deletion via `std::filesystem::remove` is performed inside `editConfig`, which likely holds a config lock. Filesystem I/O under a lock can block other threads. Consider deleting the files outside the `editConfig` lambda, capturing the paths first, to minimize lock hold time.\n\n```suggestion\n                // Capture paths before clearing config\n                std::string privKeyFile, certFile;\n                editConfig([\u0026](JamiAccountConfig\u0026 conf) {\n                    privKeyFile \u003d conf.tlsPrivateKeyFile;\n                    certFile \u003d conf.tlsCertificateFile;\n                    conf.tlsPrivateKeyFile.clear();\n                    conf.tlsCertificateFile.clear();\n                    conf.receipt.clear();\n                    conf.receiptSignature.clear();\n                });\n                // Delete files outside the config lock\n                std::error_code ec;\n                if (!privKeyFile.empty())\n                    std::filesystem::remove(idPath_ / privKeyFile, ec);\n                if (!certFile.empty())\n                    std::filesystem::remove(idPath_ / certFile, ec);\n```",
